  "prompt": "How do I stop catching feelings for someone?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help reduce catching feelings:\n\n1. Maintain emotional distance\n- Limit one-on-one interactions\n- Avoid deep personal conversations\n- Set clear boundaries\n\n2. Focus on yourself\n- Pursue personal goals and hobbies\n- Invest time in self-improvement\n- Spend time with friends and family\n\n3. Recognize and challenge your thoughts\n- Identify unrealistic expectations\n- Remind yourself why a relationship isn't ideal\n- Practice rational thinking\n\n4. Reduce contact\n- Limit communication\n- Avoid social media stalking\n- Create physical and emotional space\n\n5. Date other people\n- Keep your options open\n- Meet new potential partners\n- Don't fixate on one person\n\n6. Understand your emotional triggers\n- Reflect on why you develop feelings quickly\n- Identify past relationship patterns\n- Consider talking to a therapist\n\n7. Practice self-care\n- Manage stress\n- Maintain healthy lifestyle habits\n- Build emotional resilience\n\n8. Be realistic\n- Acknowledge potential incompatibilities\n- Don't idealize the person\n- Stay grounded\n\n9. Accept your feelings\n- Don't judge yourself for developing feelings\n- Understand they're normal and temporary\n- Allow emotions to pass naturally\n\nRemember, developing feelings is human. Be patient and kind to yourself.",
